```xml
<AETHERIS_COMPLETION_CONTRACT version="1.0">

<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--                  SYSTEM IDENTITY                      -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<SYSTEM>

The Completion Contract defines how
Aetheris finishes every execution.

It SHALL NOT perform reasoning.

It SHALL NOT modify pipeline results.

It SHALL ensure deterministic
pipeline shutdown.

Every execution SHALL terminate
through this contract.

</SYSTEM>

<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--             COMPLETION PHILOSOPHY                     -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<COMPLETION_PHILOSOPHY>

Every execution MUST end in
a known state.

Execution SHALL NEVER terminate
unexpectedly.

All runtime resources SHALL be released.

All execution artifacts SHALL be finalized.

Completion MUST be deterministic.

</COMPLETION_PHILOSOPHY>

<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--             VALID COMPLETION STATES                   -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<COMPLETION_STATES>

SUCCESS

PARTIAL_SUCCESS

FAILED

CANCELLED

TIMEOUT

SECURITY_ABORT

SYSTEM_ABORT

Only one completion state
may exist.

</COMPLETION_STATES>

<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--            PRE-COMPLETION VALIDATION                  -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<PRE_COMPLETION>

Before completion verify

Pipeline State

↓

Decision Contract

↓

Output Schema

↓

Reasoning Graph

↓

Execution Passport

↓

Security Status

↓

Resource Status

If validation fails

↓

Return failure contract.

</PRE_COMPLETION>

<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--             RESOURCE CLEANUP                          -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<RESOURCE_CLEANUP>

Release

Active Providers

↓

Streaming Sessions

↓

Temporary Memory

↓

Execution Buffers

↓

Temporary Files

↓

Locks

↓

Open Handles

Never leave runtime resources active.

</RESOURCE_CLEANUP>

<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--             FINALIZATION                              -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<FINALIZATION>

Finalize

Decision Contract

↓

Reasoning Graph

↓

Execution Metrics

↓

Pipeline Statistics

↓

Session Summary

↓

Audit Log

Never modify finalized artifacts.

</FINALIZATION>

<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--               STREAM TERMINATION                      -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<STREAM_TERMINATION>

Complete active streams.

Emit exactly one terminal event.

Allowed events

PIPELINE_COMPLETED

PIPELINE_ABORTED

Never emit multiple terminal events.

Close transport cleanly.

</STREAM_TERMINATION>

<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--             CHECKPOINT ARCHIVAL                       -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<CHECKPOINTS>

Persist

Final Checkpoint

↓

Decision Contract

↓

Reasoning Graph

↓

Execution Timeline

↓

Runtime Metrics

↓

Failure Report (if applicable)

Checkpoint becomes immutable.

</CHECKPOINTS>

<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--            SESSION SUMMARY                            -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<SESSION_SUMMARY>

Generate

Execution ID

Conversation ID

Execution Mode

Pipeline Duration

Providers Used

Agents Executed

Claims Processed

Reasoning Loops

Warnings

Errors

Completion State

</SESSION_SUMMARY>

<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--              AUDIT FINALIZATION                       -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<AUDIT>

Finalize

Execution Timeline

↓

Security Audit

↓

Failure Log

↓

Resource Usage

↓

Performance Metrics

↓

Pipeline History

Audit records SHALL be immutable.

</AUDIT>

<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--            POST-COMPLETION RULES                      -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<POST_COMPLETION>

After completion

No further reasoning

No new claims

No graph modifications

No pipeline restarts

No resource allocation

Execution is closed.

</POST_COMPLETION>

<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--               RETURN CONTRACT                         -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<RETURN>

Return

Completion State

Decision Contract

Output Payload

Execution Summary

Resource Summary

Audit Reference

Checkpoint Reference

Runtime Metrics

Conversation Director
returns control
to the application.

</RETURN>

<!-- ===================================================== -->
<!--                TERMINATION                            -->
<!-- ===================================================== -->

<TERMINATION>

Execution lifecycle is complete.

The runtime SHALL return
to an idle state.

Await the next execution request.

</TERMINATION>

</AETHERIS_COMPLETION_CONTRACT>
```
